The paper discusses the performance of Coordinated Multi Point (CoMP) schemes in Long Term Evolution (LTE) networks, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on the resilience of Coordinated Beamforming (CB) schemes to uncoordinated interference and Channel State Information (CSI) uncertainty, which are related to system modeling (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and communication (cs.COM).
